I've been to lots of Starbucks and this is my fave location. Awesome staff, great service, all around good vibes.

Second day of group orders. By far the worse coffee I have ever had. Day one white chocolate mocha.  No coffee in the drink. Next day, dirty chai. Overloaded with Chai no coffee. Employees, just don't care at all anymore.  This location is the worst.

I decided to walk around downtown to see if I could find a spot to charge my phone until my AirBnB was ready for check in and I stumbled on this Starbucks. Of course I thought, well I can go there, charge my phone and have a coffee then keep moving. I ended up staying for almost an hour just chatting with one of the managers, Sarah. She was so delightful, made many recommendations for food, entertainment and even provided safe routes for walking around town. This was the nicest store, everyone was so welcoming. I look forward to visiting this location again during my stay!

Stopped by this morning and the mocha I got is so awful I threw the whole drink away!! It tasted super burnt or something. Worst coffee drink I have ever had. First, the Starbucks staff and service was exceptional and very helpful.  I would give this a 5 star rating.  However, the experience I had this past Mother's Day outside this Starbucks was horrific and when I sent a concerned comment to Starbucks online that same day, the person who replied clearly had no idea what I was talking about.  He/she replied back with apologies on my drink order?  What?  That wasn't even my concern.  My husband and I drove to Charlotte on Mother's Day to go to the Mint Museum to see the Picasso exhibit.  First time to Charlotte.
We had a nice drive, brought a picnic breakfast, sat in the nearby park, went to the museum.  Had a GREAT time!  Before we went to the museum, we went to this Starbucks for a coffee and noticed two homeless, dirty men sitting at one of the tables, minding their own business.  I really didn't think anything of this at the time.  After the museum (2 hours later), we decided to go back to this Starbucks to get a coffee before we drove home.  We saw the same two men sitting at the same table.  My husband and I both thought this was weird.  Why wasn't any of the staff taking care of this?  Why were they letting those men sit there?  It was a weird scene.  Anyways as we were just about to walk in, a homeless, dirty man came walking out and spat on me.  Thankfully it was mostly on the ground but I did get some on my sweater.  I was completely shocked.  My husband started yelling at him and they both said some words to each other.  There were several bystanders who saw this happen too. I quickly went into the store, used the bathroom to cleaned up.  The staff were very helpful and apologetic to me.  That was appreciated.  I personally will NEVER go into that Starbucks again until they clean up the outside and needless to say my experience to Charlotte (first time) was not the best one.  Will I go back to Charlotte again?  Maybe but never to this store.

Hands down the best starbucks! The staff here are sooooo sweet, helpful fun and kind. The service can get a little backed up during the busier hrs of day in comparison to some of the lower traffic locations nearby- but this is a very busy/prime location so it is what it is there. I have 3 locations that are closer to me than this one, but for the service i will always come here!

Being that this is my preferred Starbucks that I chose over others closer to me, I usually expect and receive good service. There's no parking so you must literally pre-order and run in and out to avoid tickets. Making the employees topnotch with lil room for error.

Today, I pre-ordered a hot drink with almond milk. Being an avid customer and Starbucks brand stock owner, I've gathered from several stores that the Charlotte regional Managers did not order enough for the area and this is placed dozens of Starbucks behind. Nonetheless it wasn't removed from the Starbucks app for pre-ordering, I only say this because you do receive an additional charge for almond milk.

Of course I ordered and expected to run in and run out, but with the lack of almond milk Diane and Kenzie awaited my arrival to ask for substitutes. I was in a rush and the two ladies were able to quickly accommodate me within 10 minutes or less and I applaud their efforts. The manager was unavailable for a refund of the additional charges and the two ladies were able to deliver a modified drink and a solution, great teamwork.

Being lactose intolerant, normal milk can make me very ill, ergo the lack of an almond substitute is frustrating to my schedule and the average on-the-go pace of Starbucks customers. Similar to how the lack of sandwiches when out are removed, I feel that the almond milk option should also notify the customer within the app when ordering. This leads to a burdensome conversation on your frontline employees who only try to do their best.

Excellent job adapting ladies, hopefully your management team will help to better prevent issues in the future. Although a small inconvenience it tarnishes a normally reliable brand/customer relationship.
